catching-pen
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a small pen adjacent to the shearing board from which the shearer selects sheep; pen adjacent to a shearing stand in which a shearer catches sheep for shearing; a small pen built next to the board, or shearers' stand, in a wool shed, in which one or two shearers catch their sheep; a pen in which sheep are held ready for shearing.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
