Date: 0/0/1927
Source: Sheep & Wool Industry
Author: SMITH
Vol / Page: 70
Edition:
Quote: Two shearers usually have one pen to catch their sheep from. They are called catching pens. When the shearer has shorn the sheep, he lets it go into another pen, which is known as a counting-out pen, because it is in these pens that the overseer counts the number of sheep each shearer has shorn.
Notes:

